<div style="border: 2px solid black; background-color: Moccasin;">
<p style="text-align: center;">The dynamic nature of this wiki means that linked pages might get moved, renamed, deleted, or replaced. Old news pages remain as time capsules and are not updated to account for these changes.</p>
</div>



<p><span style="font-size:75%;">This is a series showing off news from the site, articles from the past month<sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-1" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnote-1')">1</a></sup>, and fan-content for you to check out and discover! Be sure to leave a comment with your thoughts!</span></p>
<h4><span>Fandom Stuff</span></h4>
<ul>
<li>We hope everyone has been safe and cozy during the current pandemic, reminding you to stay indoors as much as you can! Maybe even read some new SCPs released in the month of March, possibly even a tale.</li>
</ul>
<h4><span>Featured Articles</span></h4>
<ul>
<li><a href="/scp-1742">SCP-1742</a> - (&quot;A Squalid Development&quot;) - <em>&quot;Attempts to remove SCP-1742 from an object via normal cleaning methods invariably spread the contamination instead.&quot;</em> Written by Murphy_slaw</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><a href="/learning">Learning</a> - <em>&quot;So two men rode east across the desert, one on horseback, one on camel, hoping to find themselves dressed in colored silks on the other side.&quot;</em> Written by Captain Cain.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><a href="/artist-formerly-known-as-chuck">The Three Documents of &quot;The Artist Formerly Known As Chuck&quot;</a> -<em>&quot;All of our collective effort will focus on turning it into a formidable, immortal guardian of the arts.&quot;</em> Written by Monkeysky.</li>
</ul>
<h4><span>Reviewer's Spotlight Articles</span></h4>
<ul>
<li><a href="/scp-5621">SCP-5621</a> - (&quot;Jealousy, Murder, and Alchemy&quot;) - <em>&quot;Due to the immobile nature of SCP-5621, the pool complex at Calvin University is marked as closed at this time.&quot;</em> Written by DrMagnus, selected by <em>N_Aepic_Fael.</em></li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><a href="/scp-4236">SCP-4236</a> - (&quot; It's the End of the World (And Everyone Feels Fine)&quot;) - <em>&quot;It doesn't really matter anymore anyway. The hype is gone, the movement is over.&quot;</em> Written by Legotrekker, selected by <em>RockTeethMothEyes.</em></li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><a href="/scp-4192">SCP-4192</a> - (&quot;As Above&quot;) - <em>&quot;SCP-4192 refers to the nucleus of a single Hydrogen atom that emits radio waves at random intervals.&quot;</em> Written by Connor MacWarren, selected by <em>DrUnoriginal.</em></li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><a href="/scp-4197">SCP-4197</a> - (&quot;Hollow&quot;) - <em>&quot;SCP-4197 is a thirty-two-year-old adult humanoid female named Doctor Sarah Veers, an acclaimed surgeon and known practitioner of cytomancy.&quot;</em> Written by Dyslexion, selected by <em>HammerMaiden.</em></li>
</ul>
